SIMPLE: silky
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Silky
<hw>Silk"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Silkier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Silkiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
silk; made of, or resembling, silk; silken; silklike; <as>as, a
<ex>silky</ex> luster</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, soft and smooth; <as>as, <ex>silky</ex>
wine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Covered with soft hairs pressed close to the
surface, as a leaf; sericeous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Silky oak</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a lofty
Australian tree (<spn>Grevillea robusta</spn>) with silky tomentose
lobed or incised leaves. It furnishes a valuable timber.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sill</ent>⟦br⟧
